                  </persName>
             and others.</p>
               <p>MR. PHILLIPS conducted the prosecution.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18271206-217-person1177">
                  JOHN 
                  WILLIAMS
               <interp inst="t18271206-217-person1177" type="surname" value="WILLIAMS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18271206-217-person1177" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18271206-217-person1177" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am warehouseman to James Morrison and Co., <rs id="t18271206-217-viclabel1158" type="occupation">silk-mercers</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18271206-217-victim1176 t18271206-217-viclabel1158"></join>, of <placeName id="t18271206-217-crimeloc1159">Fore-street, Cripplegate</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18271206-217-crimeloc1159" type="placeName" value="Fore-street, Cripplegate"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18271206-217-crimeloc1159" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18271206-217-off1156 t18271206-217-crimeloc1159"></join>; the prisoner, who is in the employ of Mr. Bateman, a gasworker, came to our premises on the 4th of December, he went into a cellar which we keep as a warehouse; knowing he had no business there at that time, I ran by another staircase into the same cellar; I stood about thirty feet from him, and saw him put something into a basket- he covered it over with paper, looked about him, and went up again, by the same stairs; he went across the warehouse and into the shop; when he got near the door I collared him, and asked what he had got; he threw down the basket and struggled, but I held him and gave him in charge; I then examined the basket, and found this piece of striped cotton, which is my employers'; it is marked, and I know the pattern.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18271206-217-person1178">
                  JAMES 
                  LOVELL
               <interp inst="t18271206-217-person1178" type="surname" value="LOVELL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18271206-217-person1178" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18271206-217-person1178" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a Police-officer. I took the prisoner, and produce the property.</p>
